# Tailwind CSS v4 Usage

- Use Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes for all styling.
- Do not use custom CSS unless absolutely necessary; prefer Tailwind utilities.
- Use `@apply` only for complex or repeated utility sets in CSS files.
- Do not use deprecated or v3-only Tailwind classes.
- Use semantic class names for custom classes.
- Keep all global styles in `app/globals.css`.
- **All colors must use the oklch format that suits Tailwind CSS v4. Do not use hex codes or other color types.**
